## OUR BRANDS

### MR. FREEZE

Freeze the summer heat and bring back childhood memories with __ Mr. Freeze!
This nostalgic treat is the perfect snack for all ages, all year round. Which
flavour will you try first?

SHOP LEARN MORE

### KISKO

Kisko freezies tantalize the senses and will whisk you away to a tropical
vacation – no matter the time of year. These juicy treats are just what you
need to quench your thirst.

SHOP LEARN MORE

### CRUSH

The irresistible soda flavours will be the ultimate pop of your dreams. We
guarantee you’ll be _crushing_ on these frozen treats!

SHOP LEARN MORE

### MOTT'S

The apple of your eye is here – in the form of Mott’s Fruitsations Juice Ice
Bars! These all-natural snacks have no preservatives or added sugar.

SHOP LEARN MORE

### WELCH'S

Where quality, taste, and health meet you’ll find the juice bars and freeze
pops of Welch’s. No compromises (or artificial preservatives) – only natural
flavours.

SHOP LEARN MORE

### MRS.J'S NATURALS

Mrs. J’s Natural Organic juice bars have never tasted so good! These juice
bars are made with real fruit purees from juice concentrate, are free of
preservatives and artificial colours and a snack the whole family will love.

SHOP LEARN MORE

SHOP ALL

## WHO WE  
ARE

Kisko is proud to have been a part of Canadian memories since 1970. We love
what we do and are thrilled to keep delivering tasty, high-quality frozen
fruit snacks - for the kid in all of us. Kisko products was built on family
values which is why make sure to offer ethical products that all families can
enjoy. Choose from a wide selection of gluten free, kosher, dairy-free,
peanut-free snacks; as well as organic and low sugar options!

LEARN MORE

## KISKO CARES

Kisko Products is built on strong family values. We were founded on 3 core
principles that guide us with every decision we make: integrity, respect, and
ethical leadership. As such, we are committed to making a positive difference
in the lives of needy families and many disadvantaged communities.Click below
to find out how to get involved and what we have been up to.

LEARN MORE
